```
<video>
The video element of HTML5 allows us to embed video content into websites in a standard manner. 
```
```
<audio>
The audio element of HTML5 as well allows us to embed video content into websites in a standard manner. 
```
```
<source>
The source element is used to specify multiple media resources if more than one media element is being used.
```
```
<track>
The track element may be used to define which text track to attach to a media element, whether it's an audio or video.
```
```
<embed>
Its purpose was to allow developers to embed a third party data object into a web document.
```
